I guess it depends what you mean by "playing in the trackbed". If they
were doing something that made you genuinely scared for their safety,
then I think you were right to act (although maybe you should have
started by talking to the kids or their parents rather than the cops).

But realistically, how many of us here have _never_ trespassed on
railroad property, especially when we were kids?

Growing up in very flat South Bend, the 15-foot railroad embankment
behind my house was the closest thing to a hill within easy walking
distance. So, that's where we went sledding in the winter. We knew
enough to clear the tracks when we heard or saw a train coming, and no
one ever came close to being hurt by a train (although some were
occasionally hurt by trying to sled down a thin path on a steep,
overgrown embankment with an alley at the bottom). I would have been
pretty PO'd if the cops had busted us, and I think my parents (who
knew what we were doing) would have been distressed as well.

Dan
