Playing what? Meaning no offense, since I don't know you at all, I
have no way of knowing if your judgment is reasonable without a little
more description than that.

Understand that I'm not condoning trespassing, but to give you one
example: kids playing catch on a straight, flat set of railroad
tracks, with no embankment, cut, turnouts, etc., and with plenty of
easy clearance on both sides, is (IMHO) probably not the most
dangerous things those kids will do this week. I personally wouldn't
call the cops about that, unless it was obvious to me that they were
ignoring the possibility of trains.

Playing "drop bottles off a long, high open-deck bridge and watch them
break" is obviously totally unsafe and should be stopped immediately.

Somewhere between these two is the line where the danger is large and
immediate enough to warrant such action.

Dan
